The United States will press its casethat the European Airbus airliner is unfairly subsidized at aspecial two-day session of the GATT civil aircraft committeeopening today, trade officials said.    Washington has called for the meeting of the 20-nationcommittee to pursue a long-running dispute with the EuropeanAirbus consortium.    It has charged that the Airbus consortium is unfairlysubsidized by Britain, France and West Germany, arguing thesubsidies amount to unfair competition to its aircraftindustry, including Boeing and McDonnell-Douglas. REUTER&#3;